<br>
I too have never seen a pet snare.  One of the suggestions I made a while back to its spell line up, but don't believe it casts it.<br>
<br>
Chain stunning pet is very nice in many situations, but not always wanted either.  In Kael Arena I thought this pet would be perfect for the giants there with the damage spells that cause knock back.  However, sadly out of 10 summoning all I got was root pets or chain stunning pets--both ineffective.<br>
<br>
Truthfully, in over 30 summoning, I've only gotten one pet that casts damage spells.  It happen to be in chardok and another level 53 mage in my group had 52 pet and they were chain casting nightmares.  Betwen damage and stuns it was a thing of beauty to watch.  I just malosinied and let the pets go to work.  Nuked hard when we had over pulls.  Was great.<br>
<br>
In most situations I'll take that balanced pet everytime.  Otherwise 59 air pet with gnoll-hide whips is still pretty sweet--especially with a shammy dex buff.  Against guards in katta the pet ripped them up, stunning constantly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29>Magician Pets</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
